        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24636",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This in interesting indeed.  Can you help me reproduce this issue?\n\nIf possible, can attach both a file that has the data you are inserting (it can be lorum ipsum text of proper length), and then a php file that will demonstrate the issue in as little code as possible?\n\nThanks,\nRalph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-23T11:08:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-23T11:08:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24647",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Closing as \"not an issue\"\n\nEssentially, all queries passed to $adapter->query() are expected to be prepared, data bound and executed.\n\nConsidering you are building the full SQL in userland, this is not an intended use case of Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract::query().\n\nTO be able to do what you expect, try one of the following:\n\n$sql = \"INSERT INTO mytable (myfield) VALUES(?)\";\n        $dbAdapter->query($sql, array($data));\n\nAnother options might be to use the insert() api:\n\n$dbAdapter->insert('mytable', array('myfield'=>$text));\n\nIf you must pass in full sql, you might want to simply get the direct connection and pass it directly in:\n\n$dbAdapter->getConnection()->execute($sql);\n\nIf you feel there is still an issue, please reopen.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-24T13:04:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-24T13:04:42.000+0000"
                },
